I don't want to add to your confusion; when I get to this point about a theological question, I take up the Word, pray and ask God for direction.  Please don't look for any ONE person to point you the right way here...it's great to share in the arena of ideas, but I believe the best study is directly from the Word, praying and talking to a pastor/priest in your area face to face.  Too many concepts/definitions, etc. are lost in this type of format and besides, I think we are getting away from BrianT's OP.<br>
<br>
Wihinape:<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>i dont want to offend people here either...but if someone is saying i am going to hell because i dont believe a certain teaching, that may come from a tradition...i find that the highest offense to me and to others. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
